  "prompt": "What is the meaning of the ratios written on RC toys eg.1:14, 1:24?",
  "response": "The ratio on RC (Remote Control) toys typically represents the scale of the model compared to the original full-sized vehicle. For example:\n\n1:14 means the model is 1/14th the size of the real vehicle\n1:24 means the model is 1/24th the size of the real vehicle\n\nSo if the actual car is 4.5 meters long, a 1:14 scale model would be about 32 cm long, while a 1:24 scale model would be about 19 cm long.\n\nThese scale ratios help hobbyists and collectors understand the relative size of the RC model and how closely it represents the original vehicle's proportions.",
